        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Schloss Charlottenburg Palace</h2>
        <p>In West Berlin is the <strong>Schloss Charlottenburg Palace</strong>, an extravagant baroque and rococo-style summer palace built in the 17th-18th centuries. The sprawling Charlottenburg Palace was partially modeled after the Palace of Versailles, and inhabited by Prussian royalty.</p>
        <p>Today visitors can explore the the palace’s many decadent rooms and stately apartments, which are filled with many historic items including the crown jewels, a large porcelain collection, and fine artworks. Outside the palace you can explore the beautiful fine gardens and parkland along the Spree River.</p>
    </section>


